# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#  local.rules — Student-authored Snort rules
#
#  This file starts empty. Add your rule(s) in Section 4 of the
#  Module 4 task sheet.
#
#  Rule template:
#    alert tcp <src_ip> <src_port> -> <dst_ip> <dst_port> ( \
#        msg:"<your message>"; \
#        <other options>; \
#        sid:1000001; rev:1; )
#
#  Re-run Snort after each edit:
#    snort -r /lab/pcaps/attack.pcapng -c /lab/snort/snort.conf \
#          -A console -q
#
#  Snort rule SIDs ≥ 1000000 are reserved for local use; pick any.
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
